articles.description: David Nichols scored 25 points, 19 in the second half, leading five into double figures and Albany defeated UMass Lowell 91-81 Thursday night, notching its fourth straight 20-win season.
articles.headline: Nichols leads Albany past UMass Lowell 91-81

articles.description: Isaiah Washington's layup with seven seconds remaining lifted Quinnipiac to a 71-70 victory over Manhattan on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Washington's bucket wins it for Quinnipiac 71-70

articles.description: Josh Reaves feeds Mike Watkins, who gets behind the defense for an alley-oop dunk.

articles.description: Rasheem Dunn scored 24 and hit a go-ahead layup late and St. Francis (Brooklyn) sank 5 of 6 free throws in the final 33 seconds to hold off LIU Brooklyn 84-79 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Dunn rallies St Francis to 84-79 win over LIU Brooklyn

articles.description: Jason Dunne scored 19 points with four 3-pointers and nine rebounds, J.R. Lynch scored 13 points and made four free throws in the final 16 seconds, and Hartford beat Maine 67-63 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Lynch's free throws help Hartford down Maine 67-63

articles.description: James Scott and Nick Masterson each scored 27 points, Anthony Wilson calmly sank two free throws on his first trip to the line with 1.1 seconds on the clock and Kennesaw State defeated Florida Gulf Coast 97-93 Thursday night, ending the Eagles'...
articles.headline: Kennesaw State beats FGCU 97-93, ending 13-game win streak

videos.description: Jared Harper intercepts the ball and takes it all the way to the rim for the flush in the first half against Arkansas.
videos.headline: Harper steals and slams for Auburn

videos.description: Jared Harper sends a nice bounce pass inside to Anfernee McLemore who throws down a two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Auburn's Harper feeds McLemore for dunk

videos.description: Jared Harper dishes to Mustapha Heron who drains a 3-pointer and draws the foul at the end of the first half.
videos.headline: Auburn's Heron creates chance for 4-point play

videos.description: Jared Harper makes a tricky move to the basket and hits a layup in the second half against Arkansas.
videos.headline: Harper extends for Auburn basket

videos.description: Desean Murray connects with wide-open Bryce Brown who makes an aggressive one-handed slam to extend Auburn's lead 57-42 against Arkansas.
videos.headline: Auburn's Brown throws down one-handed jam

videos.description: Davion Mitchell passes to Malik Dunbar who rises up and finishes with a one-handed slam in the second half.
videos.headline: Auburn's Dunbar brings house down with vicious alley-oop

videos.description: Jaylen Barford's drains a 3-pointer to shrink the Razorbacks' deficit late in the second half against Auburn.
videos.headline: Arkansas staging comeback with big triple

videos.description: Davion Mitchell drives inside and makes a nice move to the basket for a 2-point finish with less than 3 minutes remaining in the game.
videos.headline: Auburn's Mitchell hangs in air for bucket

videos.description: Mustapha Heron leads the Tigers with 17 points while Bryce Brown adds 13 points in an 88-77 win against the Razorbacks.
videos.headline: Auburn takes down No. 22 Arkansas

videos.description: The Tigers remain undefeated in the SEC and move to 14-1 on the season with an 88-77 win vs. the Razorbacks.
videos.headline: Auburn wins 12th in a row, downs No. 22 Arkansas
